\f0\b0  Rather than relying on a single monolithic LLM, a more robust approach may involve a team of specialized AI agents that collaborate, mirroring the structure of a real-world medical team. Frameworks like 
\f1\b Medical Decision-making Agents (MDAgents)
\f0\b0  propose a system that can automatically assign a collaboration structure\'97either a single agent working alone or a group of agents collaborating\'97based on the assessed complexity of the medical task.
\fs32 \super 20
\fs24 \nosupersub  In the context of adaptive documentation, this could manifest as a "radiology report agent," a "lab data agent," a "patient feedback agent," and an "ambient scribe agent," each responsible for processing a specific input stream. Their outputs would be synthesized and managed by a "moderator agent" responsible for updating the central patient record, with built-in mechanisms for resolving conflicting information.
