\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \
While this report synthesizes a broad body of existing work, it also illuminates significant gaps in our current understanding. The successful development of adaptive medical documentation will require concerted research efforts in the following areas:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Longitudinal and Real-World Efficacy Studies:
\f0\b0  The vast majority of current research on LLMs in documentation relies on retrospective data or short-term, small-scale pilot studies.
\fs32 \super 18
\fs24 \nosupersub  There is an urgent need for prospective, longitudinal studies that evaluate the long-term impact of these systems in real-world clinical settings. Such studies must measure not only efficiency metrics but also their effects on patient safety, diagnostic accuracy, care quality, and clinician burnout.\
\ls13\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Dynamic Health Literacy Assessment:
\f0\b0  The proposed "presentation adaptation loop" depends on the ability to assess a patient's health literacy in real time. Research is needed to develop and validate novel methods for dynamically and unobtrusively measuring a patient's comprehension and cognitive load as they interact with a complex digital health interface.\
\ls13\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Development of Legal and Regulatory Precedents:
\f0\b0  The legal frameworks surrounding AI liability are currently theoretical and largely untested. As the first medical error cases involving generative AI inevitably reach the courts, legal scholars and health policy researchers will need to closely track and analyze these proceedings. This research will be essential for refining liability models and informing future legislation and regulation.\
\ls13\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Robust Cost-Effectiveness and Economic Utility Analysis:
\f0\b0  The initial justification for AI in documentation has been reducing clinician burden. However, the costs of developing, implementing, and safely governing a complex adaptive system will be substantial. Rigorous research is needed to quantify the total economic utility of these systems, moving beyond simple measures of "time saved" or "notes closed" to a holistic analysis of their impact on downstream costs, such as reduced medical errors, improved treatment adherence, and fewer hospitalizations.
